verbose_text: Genes such as IL3RA2, VCAM1 and MMP2 are currently associated with mediating aggressive breast cancer metastasis to the lung [XREF_BIBR], whereas ST6GLANAC5 is a specific mediator of breast cancer metastasis to the brain [XREF_BIBR] and cytokeratin-19 has been found as a putative marker of stem cells from the breast [XREF_BIBR].
evidence: ST6GLANAC5 is a specific mediator of breast cancer metastasis
